description: Manage and Configure Frontends for Application Gateway for Containers resource.

commands.name: az network alb frontend create
commands.summary: Create an Application Gateway for Containers frontend resource.
commands.syntax:
az network alb frontend create --alb-name
                               --frontend-name
                               --resource-group
                               [--location]
                               [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                               [--tags]
examples: az network alb frontend create -g test-rg -n test-frontend --alb-name test-alb

commands.name: az network alb frontend delete
commands.summary: Delete an Application Gateway for Containers frontend resource.
commands.syntax:
az network alb frontend delete [--alb-name]
                               [--frontend-name]
                               [--ids]
                               [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                               [--resource-group]
                               [--subscription]
                               [--yes]
examples: az network alb frontend delete -g test-rg -n test-frontend --alb-name test-alb

commands.name: az network alb frontend list
commands.summary: List all frontends for an Application Gateway for Containers resource.
examples: az network alb frontend list -g test-rg --alb-name test-alb

commands.name: az network alb frontend show
commands.summary: Get an Application Gateway for Containers frontend resource.
examples: az network alb frontend show -g test-rg -n test-frontend --alb-name test-alb

commands.name: az network alb frontend update
commands.summary: Update an Application Gateway for Containers frontend resource.
commands.syntax:
az network alb frontend update [--add]
                               [--alb-name]
                               [--force-string {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                               [--frontend-name]
                               [--ids]
                               [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                               [--remove]
                               [--resource-group]
                               [--set]
                               [--subscription]
                               [--tags]

commands.name: az network alb frontend wait
commands.summary: Place the CLI in a waiting state until a condition is met.
